This is a VERY RARE, COLLECTIBLE handgun produced at the Tokyo Arsenal. It was one of only about 8,000 total made and was an improved version that quickly followed the Type A Grandpa Nambu. I believe that this gun wears it's original blued finish, the checkered wood grips are in great shape and the gun appears to function perfectly; though I have never personally fired it since owning it. Tangent sights. This Nambu came to me from the personal collection of a military arms collector and it shows by it's wonderful condition that it was properly cared-for during his time with it as custodian. I am a private collector, not a dealer. My intention is to let the current market among collectors and Nambu enthusiasts determine a fair price/value on this particularly presentable  example of the Papa Nambu.
